1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Did you know shivering can help keep you warm?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:07,200
It's called shivering thermogenesis—our body’s natural response to cold.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,400
When we’re cold, tiny muscles contract, generating heat.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,400
But how does that work?

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:18,000
This process activates our brown fat, a special type of fat that burns energy.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,800
So, shivering isn’t just annoying; it’s vital for survival in the cold.

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:25,200
Curious about how your body adapts?

8
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,600
